---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import ImageCompressor from '../../components/tools/ImageCompressor';

const title = "Free Image Compressor - Compress Images Online | Utility Hub";
const description = "Compress JPEG images online with our free client-side image compressor. Reduce image file size without losing quality. No upload needed.";
---

<Layout title={title} description={description} canonical="/tools/image-compressor">
  <main class="min-h-screen bg-gray-50 py-8">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4">
      <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-4">Image Compressor</h1>
      <p class="text-gray-600 mb-8">Compress JPEG images and reduce file size while maintaining quality. All processing happens in your browser - no uploads needed.</p>
      <ImageCompressor client:load />
      <article class="prose prose-gray max-w-none mt-12">
        <h2>What is an Image Compressor?</h2>
        <p>An image compressor is a free online tool that reduces image file size by adjusting compression quality. It uses client-side canvas processing, meaning your images never leave your device.</p>
        <h2>How to Use</h2>
        <p>Select an image file, adjust the quality slider (lower quality = smaller file), and click "Compress Image." Preview the compressed result and download it.</p>
        <h2>Use Cases</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Website optimization:</strong> Reduce image sizes for faster page loads</li>
          <li><strong>Email attachments:</strong> Compress images before sending via email</li>
          <li><strong>Social media:</strong> Optimize images for quicker uploads</li>
          <li><strong>Storage saving:</strong> Reduce image storage space on devices</li>
          <li><strong>Bandwidth conservation:</strong> Minimize data usage when sharing images</li>
        </ul>
        <h3>Internal Links</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><a href="/tools/image-resizer">Image Resizer</a> - Resize images to dimensions</li>
          <li><a href="/tools/webp-converter">WebP Converter</a> - Convert to WebP format</li>
          <li><a href="/tools/qr-code-generator">QR Code Generator</a> - Generate QR codes</li>
          <li><a href="/tools/color-picker">Color Picker</a> - Pick HEX/RGB colors</li>
          <li><a href="/tools/base64-encoder-decoder">Base64 Encoder/Decoder</a> - Encode/decode</li>
        </ul>
        <h4>Frequently Asked Questions</h4>
        <p>Question: Is my image uploaded to a server? Answer: No, all compression happens locally in your browser using HTML5 Canvas.</p>
        <p>Question: What format does the compressed image use? Answer: The compressed image is saved as JPEG format.</p>
        <p>Question: Will I lose quality? Answer: Compression reduces quality based on your selected percentage. Higher values preserve more quality but result in larger files.</p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </main>
</Layout>
</write_to_file>